I=\int_{-\infty}^\infty e^\frac{-y^2}{2}~dy
\dfrac{y^2}{2}=z
y~dy=dz
I=\int_{-\infty}^\infty\frac{e^{-z}}{\sqrt{2z}}dz
I=\sqrt{2\pi}.
I^2=\int_{\mathbb R}e^{-x^2/2}dx\cdot \int_{\mathbb R}e^{-y^2/2}dy=\int_{\mathbb R^2}e^{(-x^2-y^2)/2}dxdy=\\  =\lim_{n\to\infty}\int_{\{x^2+y^2\leq n^2\}}e^{(-x^2-y^2)/2}dxdy=\lim_{n\to+\infty}\int_0^{2\pi}\int_0^ne^{-r^2/2}rdrd\varphi=\\ =2\pi\lim_{n\to+\infty}(-e^{-n^2/2}+e^0)=2\pi.
\exp(-y^2/2)/\sqrt{2\pi}
\sqrt{2\pi}
